The concert show at a purpose-built 3,000-seat theatre features digital avatars. AFP/Jonathan Nackstrand LONDON - ABBA fans say the long-awaited return of the legendary Swedish pop group was worth it. READ: ABBA superfans flock to avatar show in London The quartet performed again on Friday night in London, 40 years after their last live appearance. Concertgoers again saw them at 1970's best, shimmering in shiny costumes, glitter and of course, those platform boots. The band performed a virtual concert featuring avatars that were projected as holograms onto the stage.